WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.337
[♪ pop music playing]

00:45.254 --> 00:48.966
PERFECT CROWN

00:59.851 --> 01:00.978
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

01:01.061 --> 01:02.980
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

01:03.063 --> 01:04.815
[♪ majestic music playing]

01:16.535 --> 01:18.120
[narrator] The unyielding throne of Joseon

01:19.705 --> 01:21.498
stood firm for 600 years…

01:31.091 --> 01:33.218
before fading
under the constitutional monarchy.

01:35.554 --> 01:38.056
Though its prestige endured,
it became largely ceremonial.

01:41.143 --> 01:42.311
Power became class.

01:44.354 --> 01:45.647
Class became hereditary.

01:47.065 --> 01:48.233
And it held on…

01:50.193 --> 01:51.278
tenaciously.

01:52.571 --> 01:53.780
[chattering]

01:58.618 --> 01:59.786
[student] Make way, make way.

01:59.870 --> 02:00.871
I said, move.

02:01.621 --> 02:03.081
2009 ROYAL ACADEMY
SPRING EXAM RANKING

02:03.165 --> 02:05.000
TOP LAUREATE:
SEONG HUIJU, JUJAK HOUSE

02:05.083 --> 02:07.919
SECOND-PLACE LAUREATE:
RYU MINSEOK, CHEONGNYONG HOUSE

02:08.503 --> 02:10.213
It's that brat again?

02:12.090 --> 02:14.092
[♪ dramatic music playing]

02:27.230 --> 02:28.231
[gasps]

02:28.982 --> 02:30.275
You said you'd win.

02:31.860 --> 02:33.236
And yet you lost again.

02:34.071 --> 02:35.072
[scoffs]

02:36.281 --> 02:38.408
Only fools flail desperately over trifles.

02:39.368 --> 02:40.744
Aren't you exhausted yet?

02:40.827 --> 02:41.828
Hmm?

02:42.537 --> 02:43.664
Was it hard for you?

02:44.539 --> 02:47.584
I didn't find this exam difficult at all.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.086
[clears throat]

02:49.169 --> 02:51.505
You've lost. Learn to accept defeat.

02:52.756 --> 02:54.633
Don't run your mouth
and embarrass yourself.

02:55.133 --> 02:56.593
You're not even a noble.

02:56.677 --> 02:58.095
Know your place.

02:58.178 --> 03:00.138
Watch your mouth, you noble prick.

03:01.932 --> 03:03.433
Do you want to be written up?

03:04.768 --> 03:05.769
Damn it.

03:06.395 --> 03:08.730
You should put some effort
into it next time, Minseok.

03:09.523 --> 03:10.524
Okay?

03:10.607 --> 03:12.651
How is it you lose every single time?

03:12.734 --> 03:14.736
You're an esteemed nobleman, after all.

03:16.446 --> 03:18.031
Just look at this mess of a uniform.

03:23.912 --> 03:25.247
[foot thuds]

03:25.789 --> 03:28.208
[principal] Is Huiju the top laureate
for the ninth grade again?

03:28.291 --> 03:30.001
[clocks ticking]

03:31.336 --> 03:32.379
Yes, sir.

03:33.588 --> 03:36.133
The morale in Jujak House
must be through the roof.

03:36.842 --> 03:40.095
[teacher chuckles]
Everyone's spirits are high.

03:41.847 --> 03:42.889
Seong Huiju.

03:43.765 --> 03:45.892
-Yes?
-Are you aware of our founding philosophy?

03:47.477 --> 03:50.147
-Pardon?
-Why the Crown established this school.

03:51.481 --> 03:52.482
Well…

03:53.817 --> 03:55.694
Equal opportunity and…

03:55.777 --> 03:58.905
That's right. Equal opportunity
was very much the objective.

03:59.531 --> 04:01.158
Seonggyungwan is great and all,

04:01.241 --> 04:03.910
but limiting admission
to noblemen's sons has obvious limits.

04:08.039 --> 04:09.082
Right.

04:10.876 --> 04:12.711
Do you know who invented this?

04:17.382 --> 04:18.550
That's right.
STYLE
::cue()

04:18.633 --> 04:20.969
A masterpiece of its era,
commissioned by King Sejong

04:21.052 --> 04:22.429
and crafted by Jang Yeongsil.

04:23.430 --> 04:25.015
-Isn't it? [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

04:26.016 --> 04:28.018
He may have been the son of a courtesan,

04:29.019 --> 04:30.604
but he had a brilliant mind.

04:32.063 --> 04:33.565
[chuckles]

04:36.401 --> 04:38.153
Here. Take this.

04:44.034 --> 04:45.869
[♪ gentle music playing]

05:03.178 --> 05:08.600
PERFECT CROWN

05:09.309 --> 05:10.393
EPISODE 1

05:10.477 --> 05:12.020
[Huiju] You said we'd win,

05:13.772 --> 05:14.856
but we lost.

05:14.940 --> 05:16.483
[stammers] Lost?

05:16.566 --> 05:18.401
We remain the industry leader,

05:18.485 --> 05:21.029
and we also ranked first
in the preference survey.

05:22.531 --> 05:25.534
You know how underhanded
their promotional tactics can be.

05:25.617 --> 05:27.869
They're offering 50% off
as part of their launch event.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.455
And you know Lee Yungyeong,
who made a comeback?

05:30.539 --> 05:33.542
They managed to create some buzz
with that celebrity endorsement.

05:33.625 --> 05:34.960
[laughs]

05:36.378 --> 05:37.462
So,

05:37.546 --> 05:39.381
you're confirming we lost

05:40.131 --> 05:41.132
in terms of sales.

05:42.425 --> 05:43.426
My apologies, ma'am.

05:43.510 --> 05:44.803
Let's start digging.

05:44.886 --> 05:46.721
Who shall we dig into exactly?

05:46.805 --> 05:49.432
Don't tell me you want us
to dig into their CEO.

05:49.516 --> 05:50.600
That's asking for trouble.

05:50.684 --> 05:53.436
That would be a complete waste of time.
[clicks tongue]

05:53.520 --> 05:54.855
Of course.

05:54.938 --> 05:55.981
[chuckling]

05:56.064 --> 05:58.441
Lee Yungyeong turned us down
and became their spokesperson.

05:59.651 --> 06:01.027
Dig into her.

06:01.111 --> 06:02.237
Understood. Pardon?

06:02.320 --> 06:05.574
When a single ad blows up like this,
there are bound to be issues.

06:05.657 --> 06:08.827
Where there are issues, trouble follows.

06:09.911 --> 06:13.164
It shouldn't be too difficult to spin them
into a full-blown media storm.

06:14.207 --> 06:16.710
No… [clears throat]
…it shouldn't be difficult, but…

06:16.793 --> 06:18.670
If it's not difficult, then do it.

06:19.254 --> 06:22.465
Play dirty and cheap. [chuckles]

06:23.174 --> 06:24.926
-Yes, ma'am.
-Logistics.

06:26.386 --> 06:27.512
Yes, ma'am.

06:27.596 --> 06:29.306
I'm the logistics manager.

06:29.389 --> 06:30.390
What?

06:31.474 --> 06:32.893
You two could be twins.

06:33.852 --> 06:34.853
[all laugh]

06:35.770 --> 06:37.981
Anyhow, let's cut outbound volume.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.567
-By half.
-That much?

06:40.650 --> 06:44.237
Spark fear of missing out in consumers
and push the products to sell out.

06:44.321 --> 06:45.405
Make it go viral.

06:45.488 --> 06:46.990
As quickly and loudly as possible.

06:47.073 --> 06:48.783
-Yes, ma'am.
-Wait, hold on.

06:48.867 --> 06:52.912
That's not as easy as it sounds.
The units have already been produced.

06:52.996 --> 06:54.456
-Toss them.
-Pardon?

06:54.539 --> 06:57.042
Bury them or burn them.

06:58.043 --> 07:00.253
The possibilities are endless.

07:00.337 --> 07:02.505
But we'd take a huge loss…

07:02.589 --> 07:04.591
Gosh, look at our logistics manager.

07:05.467 --> 07:08.928
Sounds like you save every penny
just to pinch it harder. [laughs]

07:12.807 --> 07:14.225
Yeah. My goodness.

07:14.976 --> 07:18.063
I hope all that saving
makes you ridiculously rich.

07:18.980 --> 07:20.315
I will decide

07:20.398 --> 07:23.443
what I do with my money.

07:24.194 --> 07:26.363
-[clears throat]
-[gulps]

07:27.155 --> 07:28.698
-[sighs]
-[phone beeping]

07:28.782 --> 07:31.493
-Whose phone is that?
-Unbelievable.

07:31.576 --> 07:32.994
That's five minutes. We're done.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.663
Hold on. We have one more item.

07:34.746 --> 07:37.749
Traffic downtown is already nuts.
You don't want to be late.

07:37.832 --> 07:40.001
I get it! [clicks tongue]

07:40.085 --> 07:42.921
Why did His Majesty
have to be born today of all days?

07:44.005 --> 07:45.173
[sighs]

07:46.174 --> 07:48.093
You all know I'll be at the palace today.

07:48.176 --> 07:52.055
I'll be drumming up
some serious buzz for us.

07:52.639 --> 07:54.015
So I expect all of you

07:54.849 --> 07:55.850
to work just as hard.

07:56.768 --> 07:58.978
-Yes, ma'am.
-Of course.

07:59.729 --> 08:00.980
What exactly should we--

08:01.064 --> 08:03.358
Write up articles. Articles.

08:03.441 --> 08:04.943
-Articles.
-[Huiju] Yes. Articles.

08:05.026 --> 08:06.319
[employee] Articles…

08:06.403 --> 08:10.615
"Castle Group successor gets invited
to His Majesty's Royal Birthday Banquet."

08:11.116 --> 08:12.534
[exclaims]

08:12.617 --> 08:14.244
Killer headline, don't you think?

08:14.327 --> 08:15.620
[assistant] You're the successor now?

08:15.704 --> 08:17.622
-No.
-Then why did you lie?

08:17.706 --> 08:21.584
The ones who claim
they're all that rarely are.

08:21.668 --> 08:24.170
They all say it,
hoping to will it into existence.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.048
Do you know nothing about PR?
STYLE
::cue()

08:52.907 --> 08:55.243
THE ROYAL FAMILY GATHERS
FOR THE KING'S ROYAL BIRTHDAY

08:55.326 --> 08:57.579
…PREPARES FOR
A ROYAL CELEBRATION…

08:57.662 --> 08:59.706
ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET
AT GYEONGBOKGUNG PALACE…

09:02.917 --> 09:04.419
[shower running]

09:23.855 --> 09:26.983
[court lady] Your Royal Highness,
you must make haste.

09:32.489 --> 09:34.157
-Your Royal Highness!
-[aide] Excuse me.

09:37.368 --> 09:38.369
[sighs]

09:41.164 --> 09:42.665
[exhales]

09:42.749 --> 09:44.834
I'll handle it from here. You all can go.

09:47.879 --> 09:50.340
Your Royal Highness, it is Hyeon.

09:51.341 --> 09:52.467
[prince] Come in.

09:53.885 --> 09:55.136
[clears throat]

09:59.682 --> 10:01.351
[♪ tense music playing]

10:26.251 --> 10:27.252
Your Royal Highness.

10:27.794 --> 10:29.420
Have you prepared a gift?

10:33.216 --> 10:34.843
After seeing blood all morning…

10:38.054 --> 10:39.556
[hammer cocks]

10:43.935 --> 10:45.436
…I remain fervid.

10:49.941 --> 10:50.942
[chuckles]

10:51.901 --> 10:53.653
[chuckles]

10:53.736 --> 10:54.946
Fervid, I see.

10:55.029 --> 10:56.948
-Shall I get you some tea?
-No.

10:57.991 --> 11:00.493
-[groans] I need to catch up on sleep.
-Wait.

11:01.828 --> 11:02.829
Your Royal Highness,

11:03.329 --> 11:06.332
as if hunting today were not bad enough,
now you wish to take a nap?

11:06.416 --> 11:07.876
-That will not do.
-[inhales sharply]

11:07.959 --> 11:10.086
-I mean, out of all days--
-Choi Hyeon.

11:11.880 --> 11:13.590
Aide Choi Hyeon.

11:17.218 --> 11:18.720
[groans]

11:18.803 --> 11:21.806
But today is
His Majesty's Royal Birthday Banquet!

11:22.640 --> 11:23.641
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

11:26.853 --> 11:28.188
[paparazzo] Please wave this way!

11:28.271 --> 11:29.480
[paparazzi clamoring]

11:30.899 --> 11:33.651
-Look over here!
-Please look over here!

11:36.487 --> 11:38.907
[reporter]
I'm currently standing outside the palace,

11:38.990 --> 11:41.075
where the Royal Birthday Banquet
is being held.

11:41.159 --> 11:43.828
Distinguished guests of the royal family

11:43.912 --> 11:46.289
are arriving one after another.

11:47.874 --> 11:49.334
[engine revs]

11:54.422 --> 11:55.924
[tires screech]

12:07.810 --> 12:08.895
[shutters clicking]

12:14.359 --> 12:16.319
[♪ pop music playing]

12:27.622 --> 12:29.791
[paparazzo]
Ms. Seong, please look over here!

12:52.105 --> 12:55.149
Did Seong Huiju really wear red
to come to the palace?

12:55.650 --> 12:57.151
You know she's a clout chaser.

12:57.235 --> 12:58.569
Can't deny she's beautiful.

12:58.653 --> 13:00.238
-Go on. Take pictures.
-All right.

13:00.780 --> 13:01.864
Get to work.

13:21.301 --> 13:24.053
[paparazzi cheering]

13:29.851 --> 13:32.103
All right!
Ms. Seong has grabbed their attention.

13:32.186 --> 13:33.354
What do we do now?

13:33.438 --> 13:34.689
Now we begin!

13:34.772 --> 13:36.691
Go on! Get to it! Hurry up!

13:36.774 --> 13:39.193
We must sell out
of everything she's wearing!

13:39.277 --> 13:41.112
Type faster!

13:41.195 --> 13:43.531
Find all the photos
and articles she's featured in.

13:43.614 --> 13:45.033
You will find them if you look.

13:45.116 --> 13:47.618
You must keep searching,
and you must type faster.

13:47.702 --> 13:49.579
That's the spirit! We can do this, people!

13:49.662 --> 13:50.788
We are Castle Group!

13:50.872 --> 13:53.416
SEONG HUIJU'S RED SUIT
STEALS THE SPOTLIGHT

13:55.626 --> 13:56.878
#SEONG HUIJU, #RED SUIT

13:56.961 --> 13:58.129
RETHINKING RED SUITS NOW…

13:58.212 --> 13:59.213
…SOLD OUT ALREADY…

13:59.297 --> 14:01.382
THE CUT OF THAT SUIT IS INSANE!

14:01.466 --> 14:03.468
Seong Huiju's suit! Seong Huiju's bag!

14:03.551 --> 14:04.552
Seong Huiju's shoes!

14:04.635 --> 14:05.803
[person] That's so pretty.

14:05.887 --> 14:08.056
Those are just too cute. I can't even.

14:08.681 --> 14:10.183
[PR manager] Sold out!

14:10.266 --> 14:11.476
SHE WEARS IT, IT SELLS OUT

14:11.559 --> 14:13.227
[Huiju]
"Castle Group successor gets invited

14:13.311 --> 14:15.646
to His Majesty's Royal Birthday Banquet."

14:19.484 --> 14:20.985
[♪ pop music ends]

14:22.570 --> 14:24.489
[♪ majestic music playing]

14:25.615 --> 14:26.866
Have you been well?

14:49.597 --> 14:50.973
That's her, right?

14:51.057 --> 14:53.476
-The second child of Castle Group?
-Second? As if.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.562
They didn't even know she existed
until she was ten.

14:56.646 --> 14:58.022
[guest 1] What do you mean?

14:58.106 --> 14:59.899
[guest 2] The mistress raised her,

14:59.982 --> 15:01.609
and when she was about ten,

15:02.443 --> 15:03.903
she was sent to Chairman Seong.

15:04.487 --> 15:06.531
[guest 1] A commoner,
born out of wedlock, no less?

15:06.614 --> 15:07.615
[guest 2] Yeah.
STYLE
::cue()

15:07.698 --> 15:10.284
[guest 3] That would explain
her various shortcomings.

15:10.368 --> 15:11.786
No sense of honor or dignity.

15:11.869 --> 15:13.579
Obnoxious and without a shred of sense.

15:13.663 --> 15:14.747
So on and so forth.

15:15.581 --> 15:16.874
In short, she's a psycho?

15:16.958 --> 15:17.959
[guests chuckling]

15:22.046 --> 15:23.047
[gasps]

15:26.175 --> 15:27.468
Cheers.

15:27.552 --> 15:28.594
[chuckles]

15:29.178 --> 15:30.221
[scoffs]

15:31.430 --> 15:33.724
[guests scoffing]

15:43.151 --> 15:46.946
Wow, is that CEO Seong,
the industry's runner-up?

15:47.572 --> 15:49.323
Excuse me. I'll take one of those.

15:49.407 --> 15:50.408
Thank you.

15:51.284 --> 15:53.327
I know you can hear me.

15:53.411 --> 15:54.787
Then hear this. Get lost.

15:54.871 --> 15:56.164
[sucking teeth]

15:56.247 --> 15:58.791
Show some respect to your brother.
[clicks tongue]

15:58.875 --> 16:01.711
This is why people call you uncultured.

16:01.794 --> 16:04.547
I thought you at least possessed
some business prowess, but…

16:04.630 --> 16:06.215
[laughs]

16:06.299 --> 16:08.384
I heard your sales slipped recently.

16:09.343 --> 16:10.803
I just don't understand it.

16:12.096 --> 16:14.557
[sighs] Rumors have spread far and wide.

16:15.183 --> 16:16.350
I know.

16:16.893 --> 16:18.060
Far and wide, right?

16:18.144 --> 16:19.770
[laughs]

16:19.854 --> 16:22.273
We don't have any flashy ad campaigns.

16:22.899 --> 16:23.983
No discounts, either.

16:24.901 --> 16:27.195
Despite all your stunts
like the ad campaign, virality,

16:27.278 --> 16:30.364
and even the half-off sales event,
my brand still took

16:30.448 --> 16:33.117
the top spot in the preference survey,
surpassing yours.

16:33.201 --> 16:35.369
-[chuckles]
-Common knowledge, apparently.

16:37.038 --> 16:39.457
I'm concerned about pushback
on the high price point.

16:40.541 --> 16:42.627
But cutting prices would just kill me.

16:42.710 --> 16:44.295
It feels so bargain-bin.

16:45.630 --> 16:46.631
Just like somebody.

16:46.714 --> 16:49.133
What, "Bargain-bin"?

16:49.217 --> 16:50.509
[sighs] Unbelievable.

16:50.593 --> 16:53.012
Hey, that's just
your inferiority complex talking.

16:53.095 --> 16:55.556
My… [laughs] …inferiority complex?

16:55.640 --> 16:57.016
-Me?
-Yeah.

16:57.099 --> 16:58.392
-Triggered by you?
-Yeah.

16:59.101 --> 17:01.812
You're clearly obsessed
with luxury marketing

17:01.896 --> 17:04.023
because deep inside, you're a knockoff.

17:04.106 --> 17:06.692
I get you're trying hard
to cover up your lowly origins,

17:07.443 --> 17:10.988
but please just try
to live a life benefiting your station.

17:11.822 --> 17:14.242
[slurps] Stop glaring, you brat.

17:14.325 --> 17:16.035
[clicks tongue] I'm your older brother.

17:16.118 --> 17:19.038
I just hate seeing you like that
as your older brother.

17:19.121 --> 17:21.832
Maybe we're only half,
but at the end of the day,

17:22.333 --> 17:24.043
we're still siblings.

17:24.126 --> 17:26.087
Hmm? Right?

17:27.255 --> 17:28.506
Yapping away like a little lapdog.

17:28.589 --> 17:30.841
What? Why you--

17:30.925 --> 17:34.470
If you're going to yap like that,
at least wear a leash.

17:34.554 --> 17:37.181
A leash I could pull to choke you with.

17:37.265 --> 17:39.350
[coughing]

17:39.433 --> 17:41.769
Also, it's
"a life befitting your station,"

17:41.852 --> 17:45.022
not "a life benefiting your station,"
you moron.

17:45.523 --> 17:49.110
[coughing]

17:52.113 --> 17:54.031
We will now make our way
to Junghwajeon Hall.

17:56.867 --> 17:59.078
[coughing]

18:07.003 --> 18:08.212
[sighs]

18:10.214 --> 18:12.258
We're a package deal here.

18:14.343 --> 18:15.511
Just two-bit peddlers.

18:17.805 --> 18:18.806
[sighs]

18:39.410 --> 18:41.996
[sighs]
I can't see anything from back here.

18:42.496 --> 18:44.040
That pillar isn't helping.

18:45.916 --> 18:47.209
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

18:56.844 --> 18:58.346
-[thuds]
-[guests muttering]

18:58.429 --> 18:59.639
[brother] Oh, boy.

19:04.602 --> 19:05.603
[chuckles]

19:11.067 --> 19:12.068
Your Majesty.

19:34.090 --> 19:36.050
Why aren't they starting?

19:36.550 --> 19:38.719
Grand Prince I-AN isn't here yet.

19:40.221 --> 19:41.722
What's taking him so long?

19:47.144 --> 19:48.813
[♪ gentle music playing]

20:09.500 --> 20:11.043
[person] Announcing Grand Prince I-AN.

21:08.434 --> 21:10.352
Hey, look at what he's wearing.

21:10.436 --> 21:11.604
Is he here for a hunt?

21:11.687 --> 21:12.688
Shut it.

21:22.490 --> 21:23.783
My apologies, Your Majesty.

21:25.493 --> 21:26.494
Queen Mother Yun.

21:26.577 --> 21:28.037
Uncle!

21:29.038 --> 21:30.456
Please accept my warmest wishes.

21:30.539 --> 21:32.082
What manner of attire is this?

21:34.543 --> 21:37.171
His Majesty bestowed
this silk upon me some time ago.

21:37.922 --> 21:39.173
Is it not to your liking?

21:39.256 --> 21:40.841
It looks so good on you--

21:40.925 --> 21:42.343
You must observe decorum.

21:43.594 --> 21:45.971
Hunting season has passed.

21:47.890 --> 21:49.850
Do you believe hunting
is limited to a season?

21:52.853 --> 21:54.104
You can lecture me later.

21:56.357 --> 21:57.441
I must take my seat…

22:00.402 --> 22:01.779
for all of them to take theirs.

22:04.865 --> 22:05.991
[inhales]

22:06.075 --> 22:07.660
[♪ tense music playing]
STYLE
::cue()

22:32.852 --> 22:34.645
[♪ celebratory music playing]

22:36.772 --> 22:38.232
[reporter] The nation has been celebrating

22:38.315 --> 22:40.526
in honor of His Majesty's royal birthday.

22:41.318 --> 22:43.529
Events at Cheonggyecheon Stream
and Gwanghwamun

22:43.612 --> 22:45.573
are set to carry on throughout the night.

22:46.448 --> 22:49.326
With the day designated a public holiday,
heavy traffic is expected

22:49.410 --> 22:51.036
as crowds head out for the break.

22:51.120 --> 22:52.413
[crowd cheering]

22:57.126 --> 22:59.461
Following the ceremony
featuring the formal greetings,

22:59.545 --> 23:02.590
the second half will begin
alongside a Nakhwa Nori display.

23:02.673 --> 23:05.301
[♪ soft music playing]

23:05.384 --> 23:08.846
After His Majesty writes down a wish
and presents it to Grand Prince I-AN,

23:08.929 --> 23:12.266
His Royal Highness will commence
the Nakhwa Nori.

23:19.607 --> 23:22.693
Good health for Queen Mother.

23:23.944 --> 23:26.947
Good health for Uncle.

23:32.453 --> 23:36.957
Happiness for the people.

23:39.793 --> 23:41.962
Well done, Your Majesty.

24:17.456 --> 24:20.417
[crowd gasping, exclaiming]

24:22.670 --> 24:24.421
[cheering, applauding]

24:35.182 --> 24:37.309
[guests chattering, laughing]

24:38.852 --> 24:41.855
-Hello, Prime Minister Min.
-It's nice to see you, sir.

24:41.939 --> 24:44.066
-Hello there.
-I'm always rooting for you.

24:45.150 --> 24:47.069
[guest] Thank you for all your hard work.

24:47.152 --> 24:49.321
-[Min] It's nice to see you.
-[guest 2] So handsome.

24:49.405 --> 24:50.614
My goodness.

24:56.245 --> 24:57.246
[Min] Seong Huiju.

24:57.329 --> 24:58.747
[Huiju] Ooh.

25:00.290 --> 25:03.502
-Should I call you Prime Minister Min?
-[sighs] Come on now.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.045
Don't. That'd be so awkward.

25:05.129 --> 25:06.630
[chuckles]

25:06.714 --> 25:09.341
Look at that rosy pink floral overcoat.

25:09.425 --> 25:11.051
You didn't come to play.

25:11.927 --> 25:15.305
The Cabinet would bite my head off
if I showed up here in civilian clothes.

25:17.016 --> 25:18.892
Where were you?
I couldn't find you earlier.

25:18.976 --> 25:21.437
I was all the way in the back.

25:21.520 --> 25:23.313
And you must've been in the front row.

25:23.397 --> 25:25.024
How's the front row? Is it fun?

25:25.649 --> 25:28.277
Don't get me started.
It was so boring I almost fell asleep.

25:28.944 --> 25:29.945
It was pure torture.

25:30.029 --> 25:31.822
-[scoffs]
-[Min chuckles]

25:33.824 --> 25:35.951
-You've been crushing it.
-Me?

25:36.035 --> 25:38.495
I hear Castle Beauty's US rollout
is going well.

25:38.579 --> 25:39.580
[Huiju] Hmm.

25:39.663 --> 25:41.498
I'm sure everyone is secretly shocked.

25:41.582 --> 25:44.334
Taeju tried and failed
at the same venture two years ago.

25:44.418 --> 25:45.461
Come on.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.546
You know
I'm in a different league than him.

25:47.629 --> 25:50.132
-[sighs, chuckles]
-[chuckles]

25:52.301 --> 25:55.095
But… was this outfit intentional?

25:55.179 --> 25:56.388
Yeah.

25:56.472 --> 25:57.890
Why? You don't like it?

25:57.973 --> 25:59.349
[Min sighs]

25:59.433 --> 26:01.477
I thought red wasn't permitted
in the palace.

26:01.560 --> 26:05.272
[scoffs] Who cares?
It's not like I'm breaking any laws.

26:05.355 --> 26:08.400
You should still be careful.
It could lead to controversy.
STYLE
::cue()

26:08.484 --> 26:10.486
What's so bad about a little controversy?

26:10.569 --> 26:12.529
Nobody knows who Seong Taeju is,

26:12.613 --> 26:14.281
but everyone knows Seong Huiju.

26:14.364 --> 26:16.617
They know I'm the CEO of Castle Beauty

26:16.700 --> 26:18.619
and that I'm an illegitimate child.

26:19.411 --> 26:21.205
[sucks teeth] Hey.

26:22.790 --> 26:23.791
[Hyeon] Prime Minister Min.

26:34.885 --> 26:36.053
I need to go.

26:36.136 --> 26:38.388
Make some time for me soon.
Let's grab a bite.

26:38.472 --> 26:40.182
As long as you don't show up
in that. [chuckles]

26:40.849 --> 26:41.850
[laughs]

26:41.934 --> 26:44.520
That's enough teasing. [chuckles]

26:45.687 --> 26:46.688
Bye.

26:48.023 --> 26:50.067
-Prime Minister Min.
-[Min] Hello.

26:52.236 --> 26:53.529
[sighs]

26:53.612 --> 26:55.823
[♪ calm music playing]

27:07.626 --> 27:08.627
Your Royal Highness.

27:20.264 --> 27:22.683
How many times
have I told you not to run off alone?

27:22.766 --> 27:23.809
Why?

27:23.892 --> 27:26.270
Are you afraid
I might be assassinated quietly?

27:26.770 --> 27:29.231
I'm more worried
about your aide dying from stress.

27:29.314 --> 27:30.941
You disappeared, and he came running…

27:31.024 --> 27:32.150
[clears throat]

27:33.527 --> 27:36.280
You should just be more careful.
You're precious cargo.

27:36.363 --> 27:37.739
[clicks tongue]

27:37.823 --> 27:39.199
Why aren't you getting married?

27:40.242 --> 27:41.368
That's random.

27:41.451 --> 27:45.080
Half the maidens at the banquet
couldn't stop staring at you.

27:45.163 --> 27:47.124
What's this now?

27:47.207 --> 27:49.126
The other half… No.

27:49.668 --> 27:51.795
More than half of them were staring at me.

27:51.879 --> 27:52.963
[chuckles]

27:54.590 --> 27:55.799
[scoffs]

27:56.925 --> 27:57.926
So?

27:58.552 --> 28:00.679
You want to marry me off
and steal the spotlight?

28:01.513 --> 28:02.723
[sighs]

28:02.806 --> 28:04.182
Quite the opposite, actually.

28:05.183 --> 28:06.310
Pardon?

28:06.393 --> 28:08.061
It appears I'll soon be married.

28:09.771 --> 28:10.772
You will?

28:11.899 --> 28:15.152
My sister-in-law presses me
to take a spouse day after day.

28:15.777 --> 28:17.154
[clicks tongue, inhales]

28:17.237 --> 28:18.947
It'll happen sooner rather than later.

28:21.033 --> 28:23.577
That will make your life quite difficult.

28:25.287 --> 28:26.288
Me?

28:26.371 --> 28:28.415
I'd have to leave the palace
if I got married.

28:28.498 --> 28:31.418
It'll be difficult to serve as regent
from outside the palace.

28:31.919 --> 28:34.922
But His Majesty,
at the tender age of eight,

28:35.005 --> 28:36.924
cannot attend to state affairs.

28:38.425 --> 28:39.426
[sighs]

28:40.510 --> 28:41.845
The duties you dumped on me,

28:43.096 --> 28:44.932
including the various charity events,

28:45.015 --> 28:46.558
hosting of diplomatic delegations,

28:46.642 --> 28:49.394
visiting international organizations,
cultural heritage management,

28:50.896 --> 28:53.941
and the unbearably dull
military ceremonies

28:54.024 --> 28:56.276
will all fall to you once more.

28:56.360 --> 28:57.736
[chuckles]

28:57.819 --> 28:58.946
What could go wrong?

29:00.447 --> 29:01.448
That will not do.

29:01.531 --> 29:02.532
[clears throat]

29:03.575 --> 29:05.410
No. Absolutely not. [chuckles]

29:06.703 --> 29:07.996
That cannot happen.

29:08.080 --> 29:11.291
We're already short on royals
able to attend to state affairs.

29:11.375 --> 29:12.417
If you leave, we won't have--

29:12.501 --> 29:14.544
-Then block it.
-What?

29:16.171 --> 29:17.506
Use your veto power.

29:17.589 --> 29:20.133
A royal marriage requires
the approval of the Cabinet.

29:21.176 --> 29:22.260
The Royal Family Act.

29:23.595 --> 29:24.596
[gasps]

29:28.850 --> 29:29.851
[scoffs]

29:33.647 --> 29:35.774
He could've just said that from the start.

29:35.857 --> 29:37.776
Did he need to make me sweat?
[clicks tongue]
STYLE
::cue()

29:41.905 --> 29:43.281
Seriously?

29:44.116 --> 29:46.743
I can't believe they really cut off
cell service for this.

29:46.827 --> 29:48.787
-[exclaims]
-[I-AN] Who goes there?

29:52.708 --> 29:53.750
Your Royal Highness.

29:56.545 --> 29:58.547
[♪ gentle music playing]

30:08.056 --> 30:09.057
Name.

30:16.356 --> 30:17.482
Please forgive me.

30:18.358 --> 30:20.193
I seem to have lost my way.

30:21.403 --> 30:22.487
Your name.

30:24.781 --> 30:25.907
It is Seong Huiju.

30:26.950 --> 30:28.076
Affiliation.

30:29.202 --> 30:31.038
I am not a member of the palace staff.

30:34.583 --> 30:36.126
Why is an outsider to the court…

30:38.045 --> 30:40.047
loitering in an area…

30:42.799 --> 30:43.925
not open to the public?

30:47.971 --> 30:50.932
If you're gone in the count of three,
I'll overlook it.

30:52.017 --> 30:53.018
Really?

30:56.605 --> 30:58.732
That much I can do for my junior alum.

30:59.941 --> 31:01.485
[sighs] That makes sense…

31:03.570 --> 31:05.363
-Pardon?
-One.

31:06.573 --> 31:08.116
-Two.
-[explosion]

31:10.452 --> 31:11.453
[Huiju] What was that?

31:12.621 --> 31:13.663
You stay here.

31:14.206 --> 31:16.666
[♪ tense music playing]

31:16.750 --> 31:18.376
[clamoring]

31:36.269 --> 31:38.480
[court lady] Your Majesty! [sobbing]

31:41.024 --> 31:42.234
[gasps]

31:45.070 --> 31:46.071
[exhales]

31:47.781 --> 31:49.616
[clamoring continues]

31:55.622 --> 31:56.873
Are you unharmed?

31:58.458 --> 31:59.501
What about His Majesty?

32:04.339 --> 32:05.590
[Yun] Do you once more seek…

32:07.592 --> 32:09.803
the life of another sovereign?

32:18.228 --> 32:19.229
[King] Queen Mother!

32:22.107 --> 32:23.108
[sighs]

32:23.859 --> 32:24.860
Your Majesty.

32:27.904 --> 32:29.656
Are you all right?

32:39.416 --> 32:40.750
[Min] Manage the optics.

32:41.501 --> 32:44.337
Keep the press under control
to prevent any conspiracy theories.

32:44.921 --> 32:46.506
Aren't we taking this too lightly?

32:46.590 --> 32:47.924
No need to overthink it.

32:48.008 --> 32:49.718
There were no injuries or fatalities.

32:51.928 --> 32:54.514
The late King passed away in a fire
three years ago.

32:55.182 --> 32:57.767
The monarchy has only recently stabilized.

32:57.851 --> 32:58.852
And now, another fire?

32:58.935 --> 33:00.937
[sighs] That won't do at all.

33:06.568 --> 33:08.069
It shouldn't be over already.

33:08.904 --> 33:09.988
Why…

33:10.071 --> 33:11.198
Hold on.

33:11.281 --> 33:12.782
Don't tell me you just walked out.

33:12.866 --> 33:13.992
What?

33:14.075 --> 33:15.076
Oh.

33:15.160 --> 33:17.245
Tell me you didn't just leave
to draw attention.

33:18.622 --> 33:20.457
I couldn't even if I tried.

33:20.957 --> 33:22.751
-Why not?
-There was an incident.

33:22.834 --> 33:24.252
You caused an incident?

33:24.336 --> 33:25.378
Seriously? [clicks tongue]

33:25.462 --> 33:27.631
-There was a fire.
-A fire?

33:27.714 --> 33:29.716
Wait. A fire?

33:29.799 --> 33:32.302
What about the Grand Prince? Is he okay?

33:33.887 --> 33:35.180
Ms. Do.

33:35.263 --> 33:36.723
Are you a fan of Prince I-AN?

33:37.933 --> 33:39.226
Me?

33:40.185 --> 33:41.186
[scoffs]

33:43.438 --> 33:44.481
I mean…

33:48.568 --> 33:51.279
[reporter] An explosion has occurred
at Junghwajeon Hall.

33:51.363 --> 33:54.157
It occurred during
the Royal Birthday Banquet,

33:54.241 --> 33:58.411
but fortunately,
no casualties have been reported.

33:58.495 --> 34:00.372
The police and fire department…
STYLE
::cue()

34:03.333 --> 34:04.876
[Ms. Do] Is there some bad blood?

34:05.585 --> 34:06.586
What?

34:06.670 --> 34:10.173
Grand Prince I-AN also attended
the Royal Academy of Korea.

34:10.257 --> 34:13.051
I thought you might've been
bullied or something.

34:13.134 --> 34:14.386
You're so hostile toward him.

34:14.469 --> 34:15.887
[scoffs]

34:15.971 --> 34:17.097
Yeah, right.

34:18.390 --> 34:21.142
Do I look like someone
who would be bullied?

34:21.226 --> 34:22.269
[chuckles]

34:22.352 --> 34:23.353
That's true.

34:24.271 --> 34:25.730
Then why do you hate him so much?

34:27.190 --> 34:28.191
Just because.

34:30.402 --> 34:31.486
He's obnoxious.

34:33.321 --> 34:35.323
[♪ gentle music playing]

34:39.494 --> 34:41.663
Please work. Come on.

34:43.123 --> 34:44.165
Please.

34:45.000 --> 34:46.251
[sighs]

35:06.438 --> 35:07.439
[sighs]

35:15.530 --> 35:16.740
[sighs]

35:19.242 --> 35:20.243
[sighs]

35:26.458 --> 35:27.459
[I-AN] Who goes there?

35:29.961 --> 35:31.379
[♪ gentle music playing]

35:44.809 --> 35:48.355
If you've done wrong,
you must accept a fair punishment.

35:49.022 --> 35:51.399
Don't disgrace yourself
by getting caught in flight.

35:51.483 --> 35:52.817
Name.

35:58.615 --> 35:59.741
It's Seong Huiju.

36:00.325 --> 36:01.534
Affiliation.

36:03.828 --> 36:06.539
Jujak House. Ninth grade.

36:06.623 --> 36:08.333
You know you violated school regulations.

36:08.416 --> 36:11.711
I needed more training time.
The exhibition match is coming up--

36:11.795 --> 36:13.588
Are you a man of virtue or of profit?

36:15.840 --> 36:16.841
[sighs]

36:16.925 --> 36:19.135
Students under tenth grade are prohibited

36:19.219 --> 36:21.054
from leaving the dormitory after 11 p.m.

36:21.137 --> 36:23.556
Violation of this rule
results in 20 demerit points.

36:23.640 --> 36:25.850
Use of facilities
outside designated training hours

36:25.934 --> 36:27.852
requires prior approval
from the principal.

36:27.936 --> 36:30.397
Violation of this rule
results in 10 demerit points.

36:30.480 --> 36:32.440
-In total…
-And Your Royal Highness?

36:33.400 --> 36:35.068
You are here too, are you not?

36:35.902 --> 36:37.862
Will you receive demerit points as well?

36:45.745 --> 36:47.288
I'm here with approval.

36:51.501 --> 36:53.169
ARCHERY RANGE USAGE APPROVAL

36:54.587 --> 36:55.714
How'd you get this?

36:55.797 --> 36:59.467
After all that talk about students getting
carried away for the exhibition match

36:59.551 --> 37:02.721
and the archery range not being
meant for individual training?

37:08.601 --> 37:11.730
I got this key from Ryu Minseok,
Cheongnyong House, ninth grade.

37:11.813 --> 37:13.690
-Ryu Minseok?
-Yes.

37:13.773 --> 37:16.025
He was shamelessly bragging
about having this key,

37:16.109 --> 37:17.193
so I stole it.

37:17.277 --> 37:18.570
[sighs]

37:18.653 --> 37:21.531
I'm not sure why an individual
had a key to this archery range

37:21.614 --> 37:23.950
when it's not a place
for individual training.

37:25.744 --> 37:27.454
[sighs]

37:27.537 --> 37:30.206
But seeing how easily
you obtained this approval notice,

37:31.207 --> 37:33.585
I guess it was only out of reach for me.

37:36.379 --> 37:38.715
So do not lecture me
about demerit points or whatever.

37:38.798 --> 37:39.799
I intend

37:40.425 --> 37:42.427
to enjoy every opportunity

37:43.219 --> 37:44.345
my enemy enjoys.

37:44.429 --> 37:46.014
You wish to stoop to their level?

37:46.097 --> 37:48.224
I'd rather play dirty and win

37:48.308 --> 37:50.602
than play clean and lose.

37:57.609 --> 37:58.651
[scoffs]

38:14.125 --> 38:15.293
[scoffs]

38:17.086 --> 38:18.254
So obnoxious.

38:22.050 --> 38:23.384
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

38:40.360 --> 38:43.488
[court lady] Your Royal Highness.
The Queen Mother has arrived.

38:47.283 --> 38:48.284
Escort her in.

38:59.087 --> 39:00.797
IN TIMES OF PEACE,
DO NOT FORGET DANGER

39:00.880 --> 39:02.757
IN TIMES OF PROSPERITY,
DO NOT FORGET RUIN

39:02.841 --> 39:04.592
IN TIMES OF ORDER,
DO NOT FORGET CHAOS

39:16.396 --> 39:17.522
Must I wait longer?

39:21.442 --> 39:22.443
Grand Prince.

39:24.320 --> 39:25.488
Yes?

39:26.865 --> 39:27.949
About yesterday…

39:31.119 --> 39:32.120
I regret my actions.

39:34.330 --> 39:36.082
I was not in my right mind.

39:37.375 --> 39:39.460
I feared some misfortune
had struck His Majesty.

39:39.544 --> 39:41.588
Prime Minister Min
has asked for the details

39:42.630 --> 39:44.382
of how the Queen Mother

39:44.465 --> 39:47.802
dared to strike the Grand Prince
and lash out with such unspeakable words.

39:50.096 --> 39:51.180
So I hear.

39:55.935 --> 39:57.145
Do not worry.

39:58.730 --> 40:00.690
I shall tell him you took responsibility

40:01.524 --> 40:02.650
and expressed remorse

40:04.193 --> 40:05.528
for your actions.

40:09.073 --> 40:11.492
No one shows concern for His Majesty.

40:12.702 --> 40:13.995
The palace was on fire,

40:14.954 --> 40:16.581
and the King almost died.

40:18.291 --> 40:21.544
Yet all anyone seems to care about
is the scratch on your cheek.

40:21.628 --> 40:22.837
Am I to blame for that?

40:22.921 --> 40:25.423
Yes, you are. You are the regent.

40:33.932 --> 40:36.517
His Majesty is a mere eight years of age.

40:36.601 --> 40:38.895
Far too young
to be overseeing state affairs.

40:40.063 --> 40:41.481
So my regency is unavoidable.

40:44.525 --> 40:45.777
-I-AN…
-Furthermore,

40:47.362 --> 40:49.238
a regent holds no special powers.

40:49.322 --> 40:50.657
-I-AN!
-Politicians…

40:53.534 --> 40:55.203
engage in politics.

40:57.330 --> 40:58.957
Peddlers engage in business.

41:05.797 --> 41:07.465
The monarchy remains passive.

41:09.300 --> 41:11.135
Simply doing nothing…

41:13.846 --> 41:15.098
is its sole duty.

41:18.810 --> 41:21.396
Have you ever considered that
to be true power?

41:22.730 --> 41:23.982
The politicians

41:24.565 --> 41:27.568
burn with fervor
to claim a place at your side.

41:28.778 --> 41:30.989
Because a single photo taken beside you

41:31.489 --> 41:34.409
wields greater power than ten pledges
wrought with painstaking care.

41:35.201 --> 41:36.452
And the business elites?

41:36.536 --> 41:40.331
They hasten to attend to you
on every diplomatic tour.

41:40.415 --> 41:43.501
The mere fact that you granted them
a place by your side

41:45.086 --> 41:47.213
is enough to gain
the trust of their investors.

41:51.217 --> 41:52.260
You eclipse…

41:56.055 --> 41:57.598
the Crown itself.

42:04.188 --> 42:06.190
[♪ emotional music playing]

42:09.360 --> 42:10.486
Father.

42:10.570 --> 42:13.239
I have received a 100 on my exam.

42:17.243 --> 42:19.454
-Rise above such trifles.
-Sorry?

42:19.537 --> 42:21.664
If it be remarkable,
it is but the natural order.

42:21.748 --> 42:22.957
If it be lacking,

42:23.541 --> 42:25.418
it is but a cause for shame.

42:25.501 --> 42:27.045
But Father,

42:27.128 --> 42:30.423
is diligence not
the duty of a man of virtue?

42:30.506 --> 42:33.885
You are a Grand Prince
before you are a man of virtue.

42:33.968 --> 42:35.303
I-SHIN

42:35.386 --> 42:37.263
That is your new royal title.

42:38.806 --> 42:41.934
My royal title is to change?

42:42.018 --> 42:44.520
It is a reminder to remain true and just.

42:46.773 --> 42:49.150
Do not stand in the way
of the Crown Prince.
STYLE
::cue()

43:02.663 --> 43:04.707
This is your new royal title.

43:05.416 --> 43:06.959
I-AN

43:08.795 --> 43:09.879
Am I being…

43:12.882 --> 43:13.883
rewarded again?

43:27.021 --> 43:28.022
And so…

43:30.566 --> 43:31.943
what do you seek from me?

43:33.236 --> 43:35.571
That you be His Majesty's steadfast
pillar of support.

43:35.655 --> 43:37.281
I already serve in that capacity.

43:38.241 --> 43:39.617
Proceed to your nuptials.

43:43.037 --> 43:45.206
Wed the woman of my choosing

43:46.457 --> 43:49.585
and demonstrate your allegiance
to His Majesty and me.

44:01.139 --> 44:02.932
[Huiju] I told you I don't want to.

44:04.809 --> 44:06.352
[sighs] Fine.

44:06.435 --> 44:09.355
Let's say I concede to everything,
and I do get married.

44:10.022 --> 44:14.026
I am still an heir to a conglomerate,
so strategic M&amp;A is certainly important.

44:14.569 --> 44:17.196
That's my role
in fortifying the family's legacy.

44:17.280 --> 44:19.824
But the CEO of a mere subsidiary
simply will not do.

44:19.907 --> 44:21.450
Do you think that makes any sense?

44:21.534 --> 44:22.702
I'm Seong Huiju!

44:22.785 --> 44:24.245
[Taeju] So what if you are?

44:24.912 --> 44:25.997
Father, we're here.

44:26.664 --> 44:27.665
Hey.

44:27.748 --> 44:29.625
Must you be so loud?

44:29.709 --> 44:31.419
All you do is bark day and night.

44:31.502 --> 44:33.713
Hello, Father. Huiju.

44:33.796 --> 44:35.381
Honey, you want a cup?

44:35.464 --> 44:37.592
-So hot!
-You should be more careful, honey.

44:37.675 --> 44:38.968
[exclaims]

44:39.051 --> 44:40.052
You could've warned me.

44:43.431 --> 44:46.309
Don't pester Father too much, Huiju.

44:46.392 --> 44:48.603
He went to great lengths

44:48.686 --> 44:51.189
to find a proper suitor for you.

44:51.272 --> 44:53.191
[Mr. Seong sighs]

44:53.816 --> 44:54.984
[scoffs]

44:55.484 --> 44:57.361
So you two collaborated on this?

44:57.987 --> 44:59.780
And this is the result?

44:59.864 --> 45:02.408
A nobody who doesn't even make
the industry rankings?

45:02.491 --> 45:04.368
Shall I use him as a trophy boyfriend?

45:04.452 --> 45:06.037
Why you little…

45:06.913 --> 45:08.164
[clicks tongue]

45:08.247 --> 45:10.041
Our hands are tied.

45:10.708 --> 45:12.376
When it comes to arranged marriages,

45:12.460 --> 45:15.463
most families tend
to nitpick every detail.

45:15.546 --> 45:16.547
"Every detail"?

45:18.674 --> 45:19.884
"Every detail"?

45:20.551 --> 45:22.803
[laughs]

45:22.887 --> 45:26.807
So you also nitpicked "every detail"
and ended up with this loser?

45:26.891 --> 45:28.392
That's strange.

45:28.476 --> 45:31.312
With all that nitpicking,
you had to see the marriage was doomed.

45:31.395 --> 45:34.732
-Hey, we married for love!
-Who cares what the in-laws' pet thinks?

45:34.815 --> 45:36.651
-What was that?
-That's enough!

45:38.361 --> 45:40.696
[sighs] She's just impossible.

45:41.614 --> 45:43.741
As you said,
you'll eventually have to marry.

45:43.824 --> 45:45.368
Who said I didn't want to marry?

45:45.451 --> 45:47.954
I just don't want to marry
someone that far beneath me.

45:48.037 --> 45:49.080
[Taeju scoffs]

45:49.163 --> 45:51.999
[Huiju] Father, just be honest with me.

45:52.083 --> 45:54.252
You want to take this chance
to get rid of me, no?

45:54.335 --> 45:57.255
Because based on pure competence,
that jerk wouldn't stand a chance.

45:57.338 --> 46:00.216
Hey, who wouldn't stand a chance?

46:00.299 --> 46:01.801
You, obviously. Certainly not me!

46:03.261 --> 46:04.387
[sighs]

46:05.972 --> 46:07.640
I guess branding me illegitimate

46:07.723 --> 46:10.434
and saddling me
with a useless brother wasn't enough?

46:10.518 --> 46:13.646
Now you want to foist
an incompetent husband upon me as well?

46:15.314 --> 46:16.774
This will not go

46:17.733 --> 46:19.068
as you wish, Father.

46:20.653 --> 46:22.405
I won't let that happen.

46:29.287 --> 46:30.413
[Hyeon] Nuptials?

46:30.496 --> 46:32.540
[stammers] Did you agree to it?

46:34.166 --> 46:35.626
Maybe.

46:35.710 --> 46:36.711
You're really going to?

46:39.755 --> 46:40.798
Why not?

46:40.881 --> 46:42.675
[Hyeon exclaims]

46:42.758 --> 46:46.304
Since when did Your Royal Highness
become so obedient?

46:48.055 --> 46:49.974
And since when have you grown so insolent?

46:52.852 --> 46:53.853
My apologies, sir.

46:53.936 --> 46:56.439
I'm just frustrated
with the situation, that's all.

46:56.522 --> 46:59.483
I mean, all this time,
she was firmly against your nuptials.

46:59.567 --> 47:01.819
And now, she wants you to get married?

47:01.902 --> 47:04.030
To a woman she chooses, no less?

47:04.113 --> 47:05.573
This is downright unreasonable.

47:05.656 --> 47:07.241
[clicks tongue] Darn it.

47:08.868 --> 47:10.870
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

47:15.333 --> 47:17.251
We did this last year.

47:18.586 --> 47:20.421
And this is what our competitor is doing.

47:21.881 --> 47:24.884
[sighs] Did you need
more time or something?

47:25.718 --> 47:27.720
Ms. Seong, the thing about PR is--

47:27.803 --> 47:30.348
Don't tell me there are only
so many ways to spin it.

47:30.848 --> 47:33.392
If that's your excuse, you should resign.

47:33.476 --> 47:35.394
You're saying anyone could do your job.

47:35.478 --> 47:38.064
If it's all the same,
why carry a bloated payroll?

47:38.147 --> 47:39.482
My apologies.

47:40.566 --> 47:43.361
We'll revise based on your feedback
and get back to you, ma'am.

47:44.653 --> 47:45.780
[Huiju sighs]

47:48.282 --> 47:49.617
[clicks tongue]

47:52.536 --> 47:54.455
[door closes]

47:55.122 --> 47:56.874
[sighs]

47:59.752 --> 48:00.753
[Ms. Do] Here we go.

48:04.423 --> 48:06.092
Drink some. It's lotus root tea.

48:11.472 --> 48:12.932
Isn't this super bitter?

48:13.015 --> 48:15.726
Come on. Just drink it.

48:15.810 --> 48:17.645
It soothes pent-up anger.

48:18.229 --> 48:19.647
I don't have any pent-up anger.

48:19.730 --> 48:22.108
You've been riding the staff for days now.

48:25.027 --> 48:28.406
Listen, I know you're on edge
with the marriage issue and all,

48:28.489 --> 48:30.574
but don't drag personal issues
into the workplace.

48:31.158 --> 48:32.993
-You look really petty.
-What?

48:33.077 --> 48:34.203
"Petty"?

48:35.037 --> 48:37.164
Who? Me?

48:37.248 --> 48:39.750
Ms. Do. I am Seong Huiju!

48:40.376 --> 48:42.086
Yeah, sure. Here.

48:44.338 --> 48:46.507
-[huffs]
-Go on.

48:47.550 --> 48:48.551
[in English] Drink it.

48:55.766 --> 48:56.934
[in Korean] So bitter.

49:01.564 --> 49:05.359
[♪ tense music playing]

49:14.910 --> 49:16.036
[chuckles]

49:17.496 --> 49:18.622
Your Royal Highness.

49:19.707 --> 49:20.708
Lord INPYEONG.

49:21.834 --> 49:24.044
It appears you are leaving the palace.

49:25.212 --> 49:27.173
Yes, I am taking some time off.

49:27.756 --> 49:28.757
"Time off"?

49:28.841 --> 49:32.428
His Majesty's birthday preparations
had me held up in the palace for a while.

49:33.888 --> 49:34.972
[sighs]

49:35.055 --> 49:37.683
I intend to spend a few days resting
at my private residence.

49:37.766 --> 49:39.602
Your private residence?

49:39.685 --> 49:42.521
Then who will safeguard the palace,
Your Royal Highness?

49:42.605 --> 49:46.233
What would we do
if you were to leave the palace alone

49:46.317 --> 49:47.610
and misfortune befell you?

49:50.571 --> 49:52.698
I thought you would welcome my absence.

49:56.911 --> 49:57.995
[chuckles]

49:58.496 --> 50:00.789
[laughs]

50:01.749 --> 50:04.251
Perhaps I was under the wrong impression.

50:05.377 --> 50:07.254
Please give my best to Queen Mother.

50:07.838 --> 50:12.051
I was so excited about my time off
that I forgot to pay my respects.
STYLE
::cue()

50:14.386 --> 50:15.387
[chuckles]

50:30.819 --> 50:33.280
[Lord INPYEONG]
Is that what you said to him?

50:35.324 --> 50:37.159
It was His Majesty's royal birthday.

50:38.494 --> 50:40.162
He showed up late…

50:41.497 --> 50:42.748
wearing a cheollik.

50:43.249 --> 50:45.292
A fire even broke out.

50:45.376 --> 50:46.627
That was all I-AN--

50:46.710 --> 50:47.711
Your Majesty.

50:56.303 --> 50:58.264
And the members of the royal family?

50:58.889 --> 51:02.059
Despite tirelessly preaching propriety,
they do not dare utter

51:02.142 --> 51:04.895
a single word of remonstrance
before the Grand Prince.

51:07.898 --> 51:09.900
The people cherish the Grand Prince.

51:10.526 --> 51:11.902
[scoffs]

51:11.986 --> 51:14.280
Even after losing his parents and brother,

51:15.072 --> 51:17.866
he continues to serve
as regent for his nephew,

51:17.950 --> 51:20.619
safeguarding the Crown.

51:24.707 --> 51:26.458
That is precisely the issue.

51:29.003 --> 51:31.171
His Majesty is but a child,
throwing the disparity

51:31.755 --> 51:35.259
between him and the Grand Prince
behind him into even starker relief.

51:47.146 --> 51:48.897
KIM YEONGHUN,
CEO OF SEONGSAN TEXTILE

51:48.981 --> 51:50.065
[Ms. Do] None of them?

51:50.566 --> 51:51.775
[Huiju] Come on.

51:52.318 --> 51:55.821
How are they any different
from the men Father picked?

51:55.904 --> 51:58.991
At least be handsome if you're
a lost cause in the corporate rankings.

51:59.074 --> 52:00.993
No money.

52:01.076 --> 52:02.745
No looks to speak of.

52:02.828 --> 52:03.912
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

52:04.872 --> 52:07.249
What about politicians?
No candidates there?

52:07.916 --> 52:09.460
Why is it all businessmen?

52:09.543 --> 52:11.920
Politicians don't like mixing
with business people.

52:12.004 --> 52:14.757
[scoffs] They love money
but hate business people?

52:14.840 --> 52:16.300
Too much potential baggage.

52:16.383 --> 52:18.802
-Illegal succession, tax evasion…
-What?

52:19.470 --> 52:20.554
That's ridiculous.

52:20.638 --> 52:23.098
Either way, politicians are a no-go.

52:23.182 --> 52:25.684
They traditionally prefer aristocrats.

52:25.768 --> 52:27.603
Aristocrats? You must be kidding.

52:27.686 --> 52:30.481
Are we living in the Joseon era?
Are they trying to marry up?

52:30.564 --> 52:32.608
That's not something for you to say.

52:34.068 --> 52:37.863
[sighs] Ms. Do. Come on, Ms. Do!

52:38.614 --> 52:43.827
I'm simply looking for someone
who matches my current status. That's all.

52:43.911 --> 52:45.788
He doesn't need to be super impressive.

52:45.871 --> 52:47.873
Just someone of my capability,

52:47.956 --> 52:51.377
my means, and my beauty.

52:51.460 --> 52:53.087
Is that too much to ask?

52:53.170 --> 52:55.714
It's not like I'm looking
to marry into the royal…

52:56.423 --> 52:57.424
family.

52:58.634 --> 53:00.636
[♪ upbeat music playing]

53:04.682 --> 53:06.058
Huh…
STYLE
::cue()

53:10.437 --> 53:13.065
[♪ soft music playing]

53:19.196 --> 53:21.949
[door opens, closes]

53:26.912 --> 53:28.664
Didn't I warn you?

53:28.747 --> 53:29.790
Just look at this.

53:31.458 --> 53:33.127
I-AN,
THE 21ST-CENTURY PRINCE SUYANG

53:35.129 --> 53:37.339
[stammers, huffs]

53:37.423 --> 53:39.883
This is no time for doodling orchids.

53:39.967 --> 53:42.970
I told you wearing the cheollik
was a bad idea.

53:43.053 --> 53:45.723
Didn't I beg you to wear
proper court attire?

53:45.806 --> 53:47.850
The Royal Secretariat
and Public Affairs Office

53:47.933 --> 53:49.643
are outraged right now.

53:51.270 --> 53:54.148
-And the public?
-They're in an uproar.

53:54.648 --> 53:57.484
Is there any mention of the fire?

53:59.111 --> 54:00.112
Pardon?

54:02.072 --> 54:03.115
It appears my nickname

54:04.491 --> 54:05.784
will be trending once more.

54:07.578 --> 54:11.457
The regent Grand Prince I-AN has recently
come under public scrutiny.

54:11.540 --> 54:12.624
Good morning.

54:12.708 --> 54:14.042
Ms. Do, look at this.

54:14.126 --> 54:16.170
[reporter]
The controversy stems from his appearance.

54:16.253 --> 54:18.881
-As the cheollik is considered informal…
-Amazing, no?

54:18.964 --> 54:22.593
…many viewed it as inappropriate
for a Grand Prince at a royal celebration.

54:22.676 --> 54:24.678
He looks so sharp in that.

54:24.762 --> 54:27.181
[reporter] Members of the royal family
have voiced criticism.

54:27.264 --> 54:30.726
They argue that preserving tradition
and decorum is the duty of the crown,

54:30.809 --> 54:33.854
and that the Grand Prince's
recent bizarre behavior is unacceptable.

54:33.937 --> 54:35.689
"Bizarre"? That's taking it too far.

54:35.773 --> 54:37.441
It's not like he was carrying a sword.

54:37.524 --> 54:41.195
[reporter] Political circles praised him
for putting practicality ahead of protocol

54:41.278 --> 54:43.071
and modeling a modern monarchy.

54:43.155 --> 54:44.948
Politicians always take
Grand Prince I-AN's side.

54:45.032 --> 54:46.408
Why?

54:46.492 --> 54:50.037
Because the people are enamored
with the Grand Prince.

54:50.621 --> 54:52.623
-He's so cool.
-Let's get back to work.

54:53.165 --> 54:55.292
PRINCE I-AN IN CHEOLLIK
AT ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET

54:57.252 --> 54:59.296
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

55:06.345 --> 55:08.597
Ah. His hype is next-level.

55:08.680 --> 55:10.766
-[Huiju] What?
-[Ms. Do] Grand Prince I-AN.

55:10.849 --> 55:11.850
[Huiju] Right.

55:11.934 --> 55:13.977
The executive operations team
is buzzing about it.

55:15.437 --> 55:16.438
Really?

55:18.607 --> 55:19.942
What do you think of him?

55:21.276 --> 55:23.028
[sighs]

55:23.111 --> 55:26.114
PRINCE I-AN IN CHEOLLIK
AT ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET

55:26.782 --> 55:28.033
I think…

55:29.785 --> 55:31.119
he's quite nice.

55:31.870 --> 55:33.080
What?

55:35.624 --> 55:38.418
[chuckles]

55:55.811 --> 55:56.812
[grunts]

55:58.355 --> 55:59.898
You told me not to pick them.

56:00.983 --> 56:02.150
Well, I mean,

56:02.234 --> 56:05.237
you mentioned that arranging flowers
can quiet a restless mind.

56:13.662 --> 56:14.663
[sighs]

56:15.330 --> 56:18.208
Why on earth are you remaining silent?
You should defend yourself.

56:18.292 --> 56:20.794
Of course, it is true
that you violated decorum.
STYLE
::cue()

56:20.877 --> 56:22.462
Proper court attire was a must.

56:23.338 --> 56:24.339
But what can we do?

56:24.423 --> 56:26.341
You remain so enamored with the spotlight.

56:26.425 --> 56:28.010
But is that such a crime?

56:28.093 --> 56:31.388
Is it so wrong to want
some attention in the 21st century?

56:31.471 --> 56:33.890
Let's be real.
Court attire isn't the most flattering.

56:33.974 --> 56:36.059
The cheollik is so much cooler, isn't it?

56:36.143 --> 56:38.353
For one thing,
court attire has such a drab palette.

56:38.437 --> 56:39.605
Such a grim brown.

56:39.688 --> 56:41.565
Sure, it might suit someone like me

56:41.648 --> 56:44.359
with a warm, golden complexion.

56:44.443 --> 56:47.404
I can pull off colors like that just fine.

56:47.487 --> 56:50.616
But on someone like Your Royal Highness,
with that icy cool tone,

56:50.699 --> 56:51.992
it would just clash.

56:52.075 --> 56:53.952
Give me a break already.

56:54.036 --> 56:55.746
-That's enough.
-"That's enough."

56:57.914 --> 56:59.583
-[sighs]
-[huffs]

57:01.835 --> 57:04.046
-Tell them.
-Tell them what?

57:04.129 --> 57:05.839
You meant no dishonor to His Majesty,

57:05.922 --> 57:08.508
and you were only expressing
your simple, unassuming taste.

57:09.217 --> 57:10.761
Just issue that statement already.

57:10.844 --> 57:12.638
"Prince Suyang of the 21st-century"?

57:12.721 --> 57:14.348
How does that make any sense?

57:16.099 --> 57:17.100
[sighs]

57:19.895 --> 57:20.979
Why not?

57:22.272 --> 57:23.565
[Ms. Do] You can't.

57:24.149 --> 57:25.984
-Why not?
-Of course, you can't.

57:26.068 --> 57:27.361
Right.

57:29.488 --> 57:30.739
And why is that exactly?

57:31.657 --> 57:32.783
[sighs]

57:34.409 --> 57:35.410
Are you drunk?

57:35.494 --> 57:36.828
No.

57:36.912 --> 57:38.622
Then what has gotten into you?

57:38.705 --> 57:41.750
How can you even think
about marrying Prince I-AN?

57:42.626 --> 57:44.378
Ms. Do, just think about it.

57:45.003 --> 57:46.505
How many are as beautiful,

57:46.588 --> 57:48.382
as intelligent,

57:48.465 --> 57:50.717
and as wealthy as I am?

57:51.301 --> 57:54.054
Where else could you find
such a match in this world?

57:54.137 --> 57:56.306
[giggling]

57:56.390 --> 57:57.391
Okay.

57:58.183 --> 57:59.393
No one else knows, right?

57:59.476 --> 58:02.145
-You didn't tell anyone else, right?
-You're the first.

58:03.271 --> 58:04.272
Good thinking.

58:05.023 --> 58:08.151
But I did submit a request
for a royal audience.

58:08.235 --> 58:10.821
What? A royal audience request?

58:11.571 --> 58:13.615
Where? How?

58:15.242 --> 58:16.451
Royal audience requests?

58:16.952 --> 58:18.704
I guess you really are trending.

58:18.787 --> 58:20.539
The Prime Minister's Office reached out.

58:20.622 --> 58:22.582
Lord Jeongseon is begging
for a meeting too.

58:22.666 --> 58:23.792
Lord Jeongseon too?

58:23.875 --> 58:28.088
He must be itching to chime in.
You know how talkative he is. [chuckles]

58:28.171 --> 58:29.172
So nosy.

58:30.048 --> 58:31.133
Oh, right!

58:31.216 --> 58:34.177
Ms. Seong Huiju has also submitted
a request. How shall I proceed?

58:34.761 --> 58:37.347
-Seong Huiju?
-Yes, the CEO of Castle Beauty.

58:37.431 --> 58:39.099
The illegitimate-born of Castle Group.

58:43.353 --> 58:45.021
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN REJECTED

58:45.105 --> 58:47.607
Why was it rejected?
I haven't said a word yet.

58:48.442 --> 58:49.609
It's okay, Ms. Seong.

58:50.110 --> 58:52.028
An audience with Prince I-AN
is no easy feat.

58:52.112 --> 58:53.572
And I'm easy?

58:53.655 --> 58:55.699
I'm an incredibly busy person too.

58:55.782 --> 58:57.576
Prince I-AN is currently a regent.

58:57.659 --> 58:59.327
He's basically the king.

58:59.411 --> 59:02.456
Plus, you said you didn't even write
a reason for the request.

59:02.539 --> 59:04.833
What kind of king would give up his time
for someone like that?

59:04.916 --> 59:06.084
Then what should I do?

59:06.168 --> 59:09.171
Should I have written,
"I wish to marry you"?

59:09.963 --> 59:11.882
Stop talking about
that damn marriage, okay?

59:11.965 --> 59:14.259
I feel like I'm about to
get arrested any minute.

59:16.720 --> 59:17.804
Hold on.

59:21.641 --> 59:22.642
No way.

59:24.144 --> 59:25.437
Is he playing hard to get?

59:25.520 --> 59:26.772
[thunderclap]

59:29.232 --> 59:31.693
He totally is. [scoffs]
STYLE
::cue()

59:47.459 --> 59:49.503
Have we not heard from Grand Prince I-AN?

59:50.003 --> 59:52.172
No, both the Royal Secretariat

59:52.255 --> 59:54.758
and Lord Jeongseon
are pressing him on the matter.

59:55.550 --> 59:58.386
But he has even turned down
Prime Minister Min's audience request.

01:00:00.680 --> 01:00:03.558
Is this his way of saying
he remains completely unfazed?

01:00:08.605 --> 01:00:11.316
[Hyeon] You're practically climbing
into that book at this rate.

01:00:12.400 --> 01:00:13.443
[sighs]

01:00:14.444 --> 01:00:17.030
Why did you ask for this food?

01:00:17.113 --> 01:00:18.490
Did I do something wrong?

01:00:18.990 --> 01:00:20.075
You eat it.

01:00:21.701 --> 01:00:22.911
[chuckles]

01:00:23.829 --> 01:00:25.121
Seriously?

01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:28.583
I didn't know you cared for me so much.

01:00:29.543 --> 01:00:30.710
Thank you for the food.

01:00:32.712 --> 01:00:33.713
Mmm.

01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:36.675
Yes, eat that and stop talking.

01:00:36.758 --> 01:00:37.759
Huh?

01:00:37.843 --> 01:00:38.969
All your nagging

01:00:39.845 --> 01:00:41.555
is drowning out the sound of rain.

01:00:42.180 --> 01:00:43.181
Yes, sir.

01:00:46.017 --> 01:00:47.686
But this is important…

01:00:50.856 --> 01:00:53.733
Ms. Seong has submitted
another request for a royal audience.

01:00:53.817 --> 01:00:55.277
How shall I respond this time?

01:00:55.360 --> 01:00:56.361
-Again?
-Yes.

01:00:56.444 --> 01:00:58.530
I rejected it due to scheduling conflicts.

01:00:58.613 --> 01:01:00.574
But she submitted
another request right away.

01:01:00.657 --> 01:01:02.617
With a different name, no less.

01:01:03.201 --> 01:01:04.661
-What does that mean?
-[scoffs]

01:01:04.744 --> 01:01:09.124
The first request clearly stated,
"Seong Huiju from Castle Beauty."

01:01:09.207 --> 01:01:13.378
This time, she put, "Castle Group
Seong Hyeonguk's second daughter."

01:01:14.045 --> 01:01:15.338
[sighs]

01:01:15.422 --> 01:01:16.423
Reject it.

01:01:16.506 --> 01:01:18.925
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN REJECTED

01:01:20.927 --> 01:01:22.178
Again?

01:01:23.138 --> 01:01:25.765
[laughs]

01:01:25.849 --> 01:01:28.018
Is he trying to get me riled up?

01:01:28.643 --> 01:01:29.728
Unbelievable.

01:01:30.979 --> 01:01:32.439
Have some.

01:01:32.522 --> 01:01:34.316
We all work to fill our bellies, don't we?

01:01:34.399 --> 01:01:35.734
Go on.

01:01:42.699 --> 01:01:43.700
What's this?

01:01:44.743 --> 01:01:46.286
-It's delicious.
-Good, right?

01:01:47.203 --> 01:01:48.872
It just opened across the street.

01:01:48.955 --> 01:01:51.166
The whole team orders
from there frequently.

01:01:51.666 --> 01:01:52.709
Hey.

01:01:53.251 --> 01:01:57.130
Tell them to share the treats they find
instead of just gorging themselves!

01:01:58.548 --> 01:02:01.301
It'd be best if we didn't
have to work so late.

01:02:01.384 --> 01:02:04.054
[sighs] God, this is beyond infuriating.

01:02:04.137 --> 01:02:06.014
So what if he's a grand prince?

01:02:17.025 --> 01:02:20.070
[inhales deeply, sighs]

01:02:20.153 --> 01:02:22.364
Maybe it's because
I didn't put down a reason?

01:02:25.700 --> 01:02:28.203
[sighing]

01:02:35.961 --> 01:02:37.128
ROYAL AUDIENCE REQUEST

01:02:37.212 --> 01:02:39.089
Your Royal Highness,

01:02:39.172 --> 01:02:42.425
Castle Group,
under the benevolent care of the Crown,

01:02:42.509 --> 01:02:45.679
has continued to achieve
remarkable growth and development,

01:02:45.762 --> 01:02:47.973
attaining the honor
of being the top conglomerate…

01:02:49.849 --> 01:02:51.142
[inhales sharply]

01:02:51.726 --> 01:02:54.020
Ah, is this a bit too much?

01:03:01.319 --> 01:03:05.573
I sincerely pledge to further
the nation's development,

01:03:05.657 --> 01:03:08.284
and I hereby request
an audience. [chuckles]

01:03:08.368 --> 01:03:10.704
I patiently await the sagacious counsel

01:03:10.787 --> 01:03:12.455
of Your Royal Highness.

01:03:12.539 --> 01:03:15.458
"Executive Director of Castle Group,

01:03:16.001 --> 01:03:19.129
Seong Huiju."

01:03:21.214 --> 01:03:22.549
SUBMIT

01:03:23.925 --> 01:03:25.385
YOUR REQUEST HAS BEEN SUBMITTED

01:03:26.094 --> 01:03:27.095
Ha!

01:03:29.639 --> 01:03:31.975
[whispers]
Seriously, what's gotten into her?

01:03:32.058 --> 01:03:33.101
[sighs]

01:03:38.690 --> 01:03:41.026
[Hyeon] Your Royal Highness, Ms. Seong…

01:03:41.109 --> 01:03:42.277
-[I-AN] Reject it.
-Yes, sir.

01:03:42.861 --> 01:03:44.612
-Your Royal Highness.
-Reject it.

01:03:44.696 --> 01:03:45.697
Yes, sir.

01:03:46.573 --> 01:03:48.116
-Reject it.
-Yes, sir.

01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:49.951
Got it.

01:03:50.744 --> 01:03:51.828
Ms. Seong--

01:03:51.911 --> 01:03:53.079
-Reject it!
-Yes, sir!

01:03:56.291 --> 01:03:58.918
Ms. Seong continues
to submit her requests.

01:03:59.002 --> 01:04:00.545
How much longer must I…

01:04:00.628 --> 01:04:02.255
REJECT IT

01:04:02.839 --> 01:04:04.549
-Your Royal Highness.
-Reject it.
STYLE
::cue()

01:04:04.632 --> 01:04:05.759
But wait--

01:04:05.842 --> 01:04:07.385
-Reject it!
-Rejected.

01:04:13.224 --> 01:04:15.185
I reject your request for an audience.

01:04:19.022 --> 01:04:21.483
[screams]

01:04:21.566 --> 01:04:22.692
Oh, my goodness.

01:04:23.651 --> 01:04:26.362
Jeez, what's wrong with her?

01:04:33.745 --> 01:04:36.372
[I-AN] If you're gone
in the count of three, I'll overlook it.

01:04:38.083 --> 01:04:39.334
Really?

01:04:42.253 --> 01:04:44.464
That much I can do for my junior alum.

01:04:49.427 --> 01:04:50.553
[sighs]

01:04:53.890 --> 01:04:56.309
[♪ soft music playing]

01:05:03.399 --> 01:05:05.777
[Hyeon] She has already submitted
over five requests.

01:05:06.361 --> 01:05:07.779
With another new name this time?

01:05:07.862 --> 01:05:10.073
Yes, she put down "Junior alum" this time.

01:05:12.200 --> 01:05:13.618
-"Junior alum"?
-Yes.

01:05:14.744 --> 01:05:18.081
She requests the esteemed counsel
of her senior alum this time.

01:05:18.164 --> 01:05:19.290
[laughs]

01:05:19.374 --> 01:05:22.168
What's this now? Are you two alumni?

01:05:22.794 --> 01:05:24.087
[chuckles]

01:05:25.004 --> 01:05:26.589
I assume it's another rejection?

01:05:27.340 --> 01:05:28.341
Grant it.

01:05:29.467 --> 01:05:30.552
Pardon?

01:05:30.635 --> 01:05:32.011
How can I say no

01:05:33.429 --> 01:05:34.597
to a junior alum in need?

01:05:37.392 --> 01:05:38.560
[computer chimes]

01:05:43.148 --> 01:05:44.941
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN ACCEPTED

01:05:46.109 --> 01:05:47.819
[sighs, chuckles]

01:05:49.362 --> 01:05:51.573
[laughs]

01:05:51.656 --> 01:05:52.740
It worked.

01:05:53.825 --> 01:05:55.827
[♪ hopeful music playing]

01:06:35.533 --> 01:06:36.534
[chuckles]

01:06:39.621 --> 01:06:40.830
[Yun] Who did you say was there?

01:06:41.414 --> 01:06:43.750
[court lady] Executive Director
Seong Huiju of Castle Group.

01:06:48.504 --> 01:06:51.257
You said you had a mole
planted at his residence, right?

01:06:51.341 --> 01:06:53.551
-Yes, Your Majesty.
-Can I trust her?

01:06:53.635 --> 01:06:56.596
Yes. You may call upon her at any time.

01:06:57.805 --> 01:06:59.807
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:07:46.437 --> 01:07:47.563
[chuckles]

01:07:49.565 --> 01:07:51.067
I am not sure what to call you.

01:07:56.781 --> 01:07:58.032
You seem to go by many names.

01:07:58.825 --> 01:08:00.910
I was not sure which one you would prefer.

01:08:00.994 --> 01:08:02.036
[chuckles]

01:08:03.871 --> 01:08:05.248
Why did you seek me so earnestly?

01:08:21.264 --> 01:08:22.348
I wanted to propose.

01:08:28.187 --> 01:08:29.188
Let's…

01:08:31.107 --> 01:08:32.108
get married.
STYLE
::cue()

01:08:36.446 --> 01:08:38.656
[♪ uplifting music playing]

01:08:59.344 --> 01:09:02.263
PERFECT CROWN

01:09:03.598 --> 01:09:06.100
[♪ pop music playing]

01:09:38.383 --> 01:09:39.675
Let's…

01:09:40.176 --> 01:09:41.302
get married.

01:09:41.386 --> 01:09:44.180
My pedigree is impressive,
and my acumen sharper still.

01:09:44.263 --> 01:09:45.264
[I-AN] I decline.

01:09:46.057 --> 01:09:47.517
[Huiju] I was rejected.

01:09:47.600 --> 01:09:49.227
-I missed you.
-Seong Huiju?

01:09:49.310 --> 01:09:50.478
Hyah!

01:09:50.561 --> 01:09:52.397
You dared to run a background check on me?

01:09:52.480 --> 01:09:53.856
-Yes.
-"Yes"?

01:09:53.940 --> 01:09:55.108
[giggles]

01:09:55.191 --> 01:09:56.776
[Yun] I must meet this maiden.

01:09:58.152 --> 01:10:00.947
[Huiju]
"Grand Prince I-AN's secret lover"?

01:10:01.030 --> 01:10:02.156
[secret lover] Me?

01:10:02.740 --> 01:10:05.368
-They're even speculating you're pregnant.
-[in English] What?

01:10:05.451 --> 01:10:09.247
[I-AN, in Korean] You would marry me
for nothing more than a hollow title?

01:10:14.794 --> 01:10:18.673
EPILOGUE

01:10:18.756 --> 01:10:20.758
[♪ gentle music playing]

01:11:11.309 --> 01:11:13.728
And considering how easily
you secured this approval,

01:11:14.645 --> 01:11:16.731
I guess it was only out of reach for me.

01:11:16.814 --> 01:11:19.609
So do not lecture me
about demerit points or whatever.

01:11:30.077 --> 01:11:31.996
I'm so screwed.

01:11:34.040 --> 01:11:35.333
Am I going to get expelled?

01:11:36.375 --> 01:11:41.547
What if I end up in prison
for insulting the royal family?

01:11:41.631 --> 01:11:43.424
Why on earth did I do that?

01:11:44.050 --> 01:11:45.384
[groans]

01:11:45.468 --> 01:11:47.261
Hey, get up.

01:11:47.345 --> 01:11:49.180
Hurry, get up. There's an announcement.

01:11:49.263 --> 01:11:50.765
What announcement?

01:11:50.848 --> 01:11:52.266
Get up. Hurry.

01:11:52.350 --> 01:11:54.185
It's total chaos. Everyone's freaking out.

01:11:54.268 --> 01:11:55.269
Why?

01:11:55.353 --> 01:11:57.772
[students clamoring]

01:12:03.820 --> 01:12:05.571
[principal] As Confucius said,

01:12:06.155 --> 01:12:08.282
"Though a noble man
does not contend with others,

01:12:08.366 --> 01:12:10.701
he must compete when it comes to archery."

01:12:13.246 --> 01:12:15.289
[I-AN]
The forthcoming exhibition match

01:12:15.373 --> 01:12:16.749
celebrates that spirit.

01:12:17.917 --> 01:12:21.003
Thus, students shall devote themselves
to their training.

01:12:21.796 --> 01:12:23.631
Well? Isn't this amazing?

01:12:23.714 --> 01:12:25.550
The range will be open for a whole month.

01:12:26.092 --> 01:12:28.135
You said you didn't have
enough time to train.

01:12:30.763 --> 01:12:32.473
[I-AN]
The sole condition for access

01:12:33.432 --> 01:12:34.475
shall be the observance

01:12:35.476 --> 01:12:37.228
of protocol and decorum.

01:12:47.113 --> 01:12:49.115
Translated by Justin S. Kim

01:13:00.418 --> 01:13:04.130
PERFECT CROWN
